.B .help
in a DCC chat session to access the interactive help system.
.SH "TROUBLESHOOTING"
.TP
.B "Failed to load module: symbol not found"
Ensure modules are built for the same architecture as the bot. Rebuild
with
.B ninja -C builddir clean && ninja -C builddir.
.TP
.B "Connection timeout"
Check firewall rules and IRC server status. Use
.B \-t
flag to see real-time connection output.
.TP
.B "Module command unavailable"
Verify the module is enabled in the configuration and loaded at startup.
Check for errors in the console or log files.
.TP
.B "SASL authentication failed"
Verify SASL credentials in the configuration file match the IRC network
authentication service. Check the DEBUG file for details.
.TP
.B "Crash on startup"
Check for DEBUG or DEBUG.DEBUG files in the working directory for crash
context. Enable
.B \-Degg-debug=true
in a rebuild to get AddressSanitizer output.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.TP
Create a new configuration interactively:
.IP
.B eggdrop \-s eggdrop.toml
.TP
Run the bot in foreground with console output:
.IP
.B eggdrop \-n eggdrop.toml
.TP
Run in terminal mode for interactive management:
.IP
.B eggdrop \-t eggdrop.toml
.TP
Create the initial userfile and run:
.IP
.B eggdrop \-m eggdrop.toml
.TP
Run under a process supervisor (no backgrounding):
.IP
.B eggdrop \-n eggdrop.toml
